transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling. This is John. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yeah, my name is John Ponzio.

Speaker 1: I got a shipment of pills last week that I did not order.

Speaker 2: I canceled this a few months ago because they're not working.

Speaker 1: Can I get your zip code?

Speaker 2: Can I get your zip code, John?

Speaker 1: Yeah, 0800.

Speaker 2: I'm holding the bottle in my hand. I can give you the RX number.

Speaker 1: No, I don't need that. What you gave me is enough.

Speaker 2: I'll be able to pull this up and help you out. Give me a second.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Okay. Blackwood, Barnesboro Road?

Speaker 1: That's correct.

Speaker 2: So, I do see that you called previously, sir, and I'm just relaying the notes.

Speaker 1: I wasn't the one that talked to you.

Speaker 2: It says here that the agent that spoke to you, you guys agreed to change your orders to only twice a year.

Speaker 1: So that's why this one was sent.

Speaker 2: If you don't want it anymore, though, you don't have to have it.

Speaker 1: But that is why you were sent because I see that in the notes.

Speaker 2: Yeah, it just canceled because they're not working.

Speaker 1: Okay. Well, if you want to return the one you have, you'll get a refund because you were charged.

Speaker 2: But that will be the last one, one way or another.

Speaker 1: How much was I charged?

Speaker 2: $103.29. So if you send that back, it will be a full refund.

Speaker 1: Okay. Thank you.

Speaker 2: Welcome, John.

Speaker 1: Have a good day.

Speaker 2: You too. Bye-bye.
